Key Match Events: Lewis Miller scored in the 45'+2' to give Australia the lead
Craig Goodwin scored in the 53' to extend Australia's lead
Nishan Velupillay scored in the 90'+2' to seal the win for Australia
Xie Wenneng scored in the 20' to give China the lead
Post-Match Reflections: New coach Tony Popovic has steered the Socceroos to a 3-1 victory against China to revitalise hopes of qualifying for the World Cup
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Adelaide Oval in Adelaide, Australia, in front of 46,219 spectators
